{"id":1089031114,"question_id":2777,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"4 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1698834491,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"5 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1089031114/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Distinct Difference Array","memory":"44.2 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int[] distinctDifferenceArray(int[] nums) {\n\n        Set<Integer> preS = new HashSet<>();\n        Set<Integer> sufS = new HashSet<>();\n        int[] res = new int[nums.length];\n        int[] sufA = new int[nums.length + 1];\n        int count = 0;\n\n        for (int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){\n\n            if (!preS.contains(nums[i])){\n                  preS.add(nums[i]);\n                  count++;        \n            }\n\n            res[i] = count;\n\n        }\n\n        count = 0;\n\n        for (int i=nums.length-1; i >= 0; i--){\n\n            if (!sufS.contains(nums[i])){\n                  sufS.add(nums[i]);\n                  count++;        \n            }\n\n            sufA[i] = count;\n\n        }\n\n        for (int i=0; i<nums.length; i++){\n\n            res[i] -= sufA[i+1];\n\n        }\n        \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-distinct-difference-array","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
